The paper focuses on the development of a deep neural model for emotion appraisal in social robots, which involves aspects of robotics (cs.RO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of deep neural networks and the evaluation of the proposed model with different challenging corpora also suggest the relevance of these sub-categories.
